<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-04-23T17:04:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-04-23T17:04:00-05:00" n="726" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d726">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/11651.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Consul <persName type="from">Letcher</persName> to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Chihuahua</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-04-23T15:00:00-07:04">
                                    <hi rend="italic">April 23, 1914, 3 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>The Constitutionalist Chief has requested me verbally to ask if the
                            President will consider receiving from him a High Commissioner
                            authorized to treat upon the state of affairs and clothed with full
                            power, or, if not convenient to receive such a Commissioner personally,
                            that each appoint such a High Commissioner for the purpose named.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Letcher</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>